{"name":"Performance","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>The ability to perform in front of a crowd by using tricks or other feats to entertain them. The Puppeteer, musician and street actor all have this skill. A basic performance art must be chosen when acquiring this skill. The possible applications of performance include but are not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drama: Acting, mime and puppetry.</li>\n<li>Trickery: Sleight of hand, street magic, fortune telling, fire-breathing and ventriloquism.</li>\n<li>Music: Dancing, musical instrument and singing.</li>\n<li>Oratory: Storytelling, poetry and prose.</li>\n<li>Corporal: Clowning, juggling and contortion.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This skill is essential for buskers, bards and minstrels.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Any specific performance art or musical instrument.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3DWLnML5WOqGQgF5"}
{"name":"Commerce","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Commerce is the ability to trade, appraise, buy and sell goods. In addition to bartering characters can use the commerce skill for the following actions: Evaluating trade routes, identifying potential markets and buyers, negotiating trading agreements and appraising items. Successful bartering confers a 10% price decrease per roll difference (up to 30%) rather than the customary 5%.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Fields of expertise such as spices, slaves, et cetera.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"42IcqWHV7k2q1YlJ"}
{"name":"Common Lore","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Common lore is basic knowledge about a chosen subject, a culture, species or world &ndash; and this skill gives insight into the subject matter such as habits, traditions, religious practices and other noteworthy information related to the chosen subject. Common lore is usually acquired through interaction with the given subject, not through scholarly studies. For instance, common lore about the Great Empire of Og&eacute; would grant the character knowledge about the societal structure, the culture and traditions in Og&eacute; civilisation, familiarity with the civil war and subsequent exile of the Virgin Empress and the prominent karmic belief of the species. Lore about the underworld of Llyhn would grant understanding of organised crime, the thieves&rsquo; code, division of the city between the gangs, popular hangouts, well-known contacts and smugglers as well as the unofficial hierarchy.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Any subject &ndash; granting specific insight into a niche area of the subject.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"B08az9TBv7qEbx0s"}
{"name":"Intrigue","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Intrigue is the clandestine and sometimes illicit social interaction between persons. This skill grants the ability to better discover secret agendas and craftily achieve your own (usually sinister) ends through subtle persuasion of people.</p>\n<p>This skill is particularly useful for the aristocracy, lawmakers and underworld personas. The knowledge is generally applied to behaviour within civic administration but can also relate to all sentient beings&rsquo; group interactions.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Politics - knowledge of the processes involved with groups of people make decisions in society, thereby increasing the chance of getting your own way by using the system to achieve your goals.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Drjpj6EDYlbxrZLJ"}
{"name":"Navigation","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>The navigation skill is employed whenever a character tries to read a map, make use of directions or use known landmarks to find her way in unfamiliar territory or under unusual circumstances. Navigation can also help pinpoint a current position with high accuracy if a visible point of reference such as heavenly constellations or similar is available. Furthermore, the navigation skill is used when trying to charter a course, calculate routes, estimating travelling time and producing maps.</p>\n<p>This skill is useful for Scouts, cartographers and seafarers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Orienteering and cartography.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LHEechhbG25ngYkX"}
{"name":"Herbalism","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Herbalism is the knowledge of herbs, fungi and other plants with nutritional, aphrodisiacal, hallucinogenic, remedial or detrimental properties. Herbalism allows a character to identify and distinguish between numerous plants and furthermore to curate and prepare these to create various balms, teas, ointments, poisons, healing salves, herbal incense and the like. Tea rituals and herbal baths are an integral part of the cultural customs in Llyhn, making herbalists valuable people.</p>\n<p>Herbalism is particularly important for healers, assassins, cooks, tea infusers and celebrants.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Poisons, remedial herbs, tea, spices and balms.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LXHLt6UAmsizo7IX"}
{"name":"Cryptography","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Cryptography deals with the understanding and sometimes practical use of covert communication. This skill allows the character to detect, decipher or convey secret codes, symbols and signs when they are encountered. Using obscure methods to convey threats, warnings and other information are common among various sects and others who wish to keep their communication secret from outsiders. Covert information can take many forms; from hand signals and body language to obscure symbols and sophisticated codes. The sects in Llyhn often use written symbols and codes - which are incomprehensible to others - as a means of communication. Assassins and thieves working in unison often use hand signals and other gesticulation to communicate silently and unnoticeably (commonly called the Thieves nod).</p>\n<p>Clothing style and wearing specific garments may also transmit information about the intent and purpose of one&rsquo;s presence. The character has insight into the general field of cryptography and can decipher basic messages and occasionally discover hidden meanings in observed phenomena and writing. Specialisation is needed to be able to detect, understand or inscribe/give secret information from/to a particular group.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Sects and cults, dead languages, the thieves nod, cultural jargon, secret tongue - The secret tongue is a self-invented code language only known to the character and those individuals she chooses to induct &ndash; these characters must also spend points to obtain this skill and speciality. A secret tongue can either be an entirely new language or a type of code integrated into an existing language making only the initiated able to detect and comprehend it.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PGkHepYMP7950ud7"}
{"name":"Occult Lore","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Which horrors inhabit the eternal expanse of the Void, what grotesque rituals are performed by screaming priestesses to appease the mad apparitions of their mindless masters and to serve which bizarre purpose do the Yiagh&rsquo;Zii perform their deranged dances on pernicious peaks? Occult lore is knowledge with dangerous subject matter; the understanding of topics which make lesser beings lose their minds. Characters with this sort of insight have acquired it from old dusty tablets, listening to the ramblings of the deranged and fanatical prophets or by the first-hand experience of horrendous practices, creatures or places.</p>\n<p>This skill can grant insight into blood rituals, entities of the Void and other abhorrent or occult subjects and practices with which the residents of Llyhn are occasionally faced. Voidfarers, scholars and devout servants of secret cults mostly possess occult lore.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Void entities and specific cults.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PSX6HxG0wH8i8S1d"}
{"name":"Anatomy","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Anatomy is the understanding of how bodies function. The anatomy skill has two main foci: One is treating injuries, alleviating and curing diseases, setting bones as well as performing surgery. The other is using the knowledge for rudimentary or detrimental purposes; knowing how various substances affect the body and so on or effectively incapacitating or hurting others.</p>\n<p>As anatomy differs the player must choose a species that the skill applies to; they may attempt to use the skill for other species, but suffer a penalty depending on the similarity or divergence between the species.</p>\n<p>Characters versed in anatomy may apply their INT modifier as a bonus to damage rolls and other rolls benefitting from an understanding of how bodies function. Anatomy is useful for physicians, shamans, herbalists, scholars and mercenaries.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Surgery, bone setting and torture.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PsCDKdX2iBkTGK9T"}
{"name":"Subterfuge","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Subterfuge is used when your character intentionally attempts to deceive someone or misrepresent the true nature of an activity or object. This skill should be used if your character wants to mislead people, create forgeries and disguises. The time and effort needed to create disguises and forgeries depend on the complexity and level of detail you want to apply to the task. Proper materials must be available, and a place to work is also essential. It is possible to masquerade as almost anything with vaguely the same body-structure as your character; opposite gender, another species or a specific person are all possibilities although they are quite difficult to achieve.</p>\n<p>This skill is useful for con artists, thieves and spies.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Disguises &ndash; this specialisation enables the character to create viable disguises with few materials or with extreme accuracy. Forgery &ndash; allow characters to create counterfeits almost undetectable from the genuine article.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q0VxNWCmMkxDZDj0"}
{"name":"Survival","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill covers a profound understanding of nature, flora, fauna, weather phenomena and the various aptitudes needed to survive in the wild. This includes the ability to create shelter, forage, fish and hunt, ascertaining safe sleeping locations and so on. Additionally, survival enables characters to find accessible trails and quick passage when travelling in natural habitats.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Particular environments and climates.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QvWA3FVi7iml1OtI"}
{"name":"Expression","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Expression is the art of using oratory abilities to make an impression on someone. Delivering a message in a clear and comprehensive manner is a craft - doing it with style is an art. Expression is such an art. Expression is applicable when characters want to convince someone to do something or influence their point of view. Expression increases the ability to encourage a particular belief or action from another being. It is used when a character wishes to guide people toward the embracing of an idea or attitude by rational and symbolic means.</p>\n<p>Street preachers, poets, delegates, lawmakers and scholars often use this skill.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Public speaking and diplomacy - the subtle and skilful handling of negotiations, alliances, treaties and agreements as well as the art and practice of using tact and conversation to resolve conflicts.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QxQeIxzo44RON3qh"}
{"name":"Languages","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Most beings in Llyhn speak some form of the dialect known as Darij, but most of the residents &ndash; and all otherworlders &ndash; also have a native language. Characters are always able to speak low-Darij - the principal tongue of the common and low-castes - to communicate with the residents in Llyhn. Languages of other species - including High-Darij and Akkadian - can be purchased and give the character the ability to understand and speak those languages. The literacy specialisation can be bought for three points without acquiring the language skill if a player wants his or her character to be able to read and scribble the pictographic writings of low-Darij.</p>\n<p>Languages are useful for merchants, scholars, clerks and other people who deal with otherworlders on a regular basis.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Literacy &ndash; the ability to read and write. If the character speaks Akkadian he or she would be eligible to be literate in cuneiform.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Rmvb2ms99XVl8s78"}
{"name":"Larceny","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Theft and robbery are everyday happenings in Llyhn, and most residents in the slum-district Kimah and other poor neighbourhoods are at least familiar with the larceny skill. Larceny encompasses most skills employed by the thieving and pilfering gits of Llyhn: the art of lock- picking, setting and disarming traps, hiding stolen goods, picking pockets, swindling, et cetera. Some actions, like picking a lock require the proper tools where others just need opportunity. Most actions involving larceny only require one skill-roll, whereas an elaborate swindle act will involve several rolls.</p>\n<p>Larceny is useful to pick-pockets, cat-thieves and beggars.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Lock- picking, traps, games (swindling) and picking pockets &ndash; granting the ability to for instance pilfer items while conversing with the victim.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UBPGZJ6uAAG9tTSH"}
{"name":"Rituals","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Who would dare offend the ancestors with a poorly performed sacrifice, which Deity would look kindly upon a worshipper who does not know the proper honours to pay and what courtesan could ever hope of being employed if she does not know the appropriate rituals of her trade? This skill grants insight and the ability to identify and understand ceremonies and rituals involved in for instance ancestral worship, temple procedures and other aspects of daily life in Llyhn. For characters to be able to perform rituals and ceremonies, they must specialise in those specific types of ritualistic practices, such as sacrifices, temple dancing and so on.</p>\n<p>This skill is valuable for courtesans, scholars, blood ritualists, ancestral celebrants and temple dancers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Channelling rituals, blood rites, temple dances, ceremonial sacrifice, deity worship, courtesan training and tea ceremony. Channelling Rituals &ndash; this specialisation allows a Gnostic character to apply a +1 modifier to all channelling and to reduce the channelling time by one step. Ritualistic sacrifice - practitioners of Blood Rituals may add a +1 modifier to ritual rolls. Courtesan rituals - this specialisation enables the character to perform and practice the rituals of a courtesan in Llyhn.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UxV6roL0KncfiaIz"}
{"name":"Trade Skills","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill grants the character proficiency within a given craft or trade. He or she knows the theory as well as the practical application of the chosen trade and is able to make a living from it. When acquiring this skill, you must decide which specific craft you want. Most residents in Llyhn have at least a basic understanding of a trade; it is the profession, which provides their livelihood. Trades can be used in various ways: To work using your trade and thus making a salary (one skill-roll), for crafting, repairing or improving items (usually several skill-rolls), if you want to use your knowledge about the trade such as when identifying the origin of a specific item, evaluating its quality, explaining the best application of a given tool, et cetera. A specific trade must be chosen either from the list below or as agreed with the Arbiter.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Agriculture: Knowledge of growing crops, farming and tending livestock.</li>\n<li>Alchemy: The practice of enriching, maturing, refining and coalescing natural materials to obtain useful resources.</li>\n<li>Armourer: The ability to create, repair, improve and evaluate amour.</li>\n<li>Artistic: The ability to produce works of art by painting, writing, composing, sculpturing or carving.</li>\n<li>Blacksmith: The ability to create tools and items from iron and other metals.</li>\n<li>Bowyer: The ability to create, repair and improve upon bows and arrows.</li>\n<li>Brewing: The knowledge about and ability to brew beer and other alcoholic beverages.</li>\n<li>Carpentry: The ability to do woodworking, build houses, wagons, etc.</li>\n<li>Cooking: The knowledge about food and the ability to create flavourful meals.</li>\n<li>Engineering: Knowledge of designing and building land-based structures and apparatus&rsquo; such as houses, waterwheels, ballistae and so on.</li>\n<li>Fishing: The ability to fish using nets, hooks, spears or any other applicable method.</li>\n<li>Hunting: The ability to hunt game and fowls using bow, spear, snares or any other appropriate method.</li>\n<li>Jeweller: The ability to create, repair and evaluate jewellery.</li>\n<li>Leatherworking: the ability to create items in leather, such as clothing, armour, footwear, saddles, etc.</li>\n<li>Masonry: The ability to build stone structures.</li>\n<li>Mining: The ability to spot possible mining locations and supervise mining activities once a mine has been set up.</li>\n<li>Sailing: The ability to control and manage water going vessels.</li>\n<li>Shipwright: Knowledge of designing and building boats and ships.</li>\n<li>Tailoring: The ability to design, sew and embroider any clothing or textile.</li>\n<li>Weaving: The ability to design and weave and repair garments, draperies, carpets and tapestries.</li>\n<li>Weaponsmith: The ability to create, repair and improve metal weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The trade skill is particularly useful for craftsman, labourers and slaves.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Jeweller and weaponsmith.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XJBBLKvFgOise3wP"}
{"name":"Stealth","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>The ability to move undetected, hiding and otherwise avoiding notice. To successfully stay undetected suitable terrain, objects or conditions - such as the cover of darkness - must be present. This skill is used when your character attempts to blend into a crowd, shadow someone, hide from prying eyes or cover her tracks from a pursuer. Stealth actions are usually contested with the opposing individual using his Awareness as the basis.</p>\n<p>This skill is particularly useful to scouts, thieves and assassins.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Blending &ndash; this specialisation enables a character to easily disappear in a crowd, adopting the gait, posture and semblance of the surrounding people. Obscure tracks &ndash; this specialisation enables the character to completely remove tracks or to misdirect anyone who might pursue them.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YlWVfqNyhr3TUIZb"}
{"name":"Athletics","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>The athletics skill covers a wide range of physical capabilities such as running, jumping, swimming, climbing and throwing. This skill is used for any action, which requires extensive or extraordinary physical exertion. Which trait is applicable for athletic activities depends entirely on the feat being attempted: A long march action may rely on Stamina where leaping between rooftops would apply the Strength Trait.</p>\n<p>This skill is particularly useful for hunters, mercenaries, rangers and messengers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Throwing, running, swimming, climbing and jumping. The Throwing specialisation allows a character a +1 to the throwing range multiplier.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZKBbkD9NtH32dTvP"}
{"name":"Intimidation","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Intimidation is employed when a character wants to coerce, discourage, impede or simply frighten people. The purpose of intimidation is to compel someone to do what you want by using direct or subtle threats. You need only make a skill-roll if you have a specific intent with a threat. If an intimidation attempt is based on subtle means such as blackmail, it is possible &ndash; at the Arbiter&rsquo;s discretion &ndash; to use Traits, such as Persuasion, as bases for the action.</p>\n<p>This skill is especially useful to thugs, guards and occasionally diplomats.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: The Silent treatment &ndash; subtle intimidation using only threatening demeanour and menacing stares allows the character to coerce people without anyone else noticing. The silent treatment is based on Presence rather.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dWv73BfPKq2jgx4z"}
{"name":"Enquiry","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill involves investigating through asking questions, doing research, finding key people with relevant information and appraising the value and truthfulness of discovered information. Knowing whom to ask and the right questions to ask is vital - the enquiry skill allows prompt, thorough and systematic investigations. The enquiry skill works differently in various scenarios: Firstly, it is the ability to get basic information about local activities by picking up rumours, information and the occasional secret through casual conversation andmaybe buying a few pitchers of kelp wine. Secondly, it is the ability to make a focused search into a specified topic by doing research, finding key people with relevant information, studying and perhaps &ndash; if all else fails - the occasional interrogation.</p>\n<p>Enquiry is useful for guardsmen, clerks, scholars and thieves.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Interrogation &ndash; gaining information from unwilling subjects without resorting to intimidation or direct violence. Casual conversation - the art of tricking a person into giving up his secrets without realising it.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hBPkfWfw74ru8vNK"}
{"name":"Socialise","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Social competence can be as imperative to character survival as the ability to swing a scimitar. The socialise skill confers the ability to effortlessly mingle and partake in social situations while steering conversations, subtly influencing the mood or otherwise pushing an agenda. The socialise skill provides the habits necessary for acting and participating in society in keeping with moral norms, attitudes, values, motives and social roles.</p>\n<p><em>This skill is especially practical for delegates, spies, aristocrats, and diplomats. </em></p>\n<p>Suggested specialisations: Etiquette, tavern chatter, high caste conversation and low Caste babble.</p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hbsB29eZUq2Ckw7j"}
{"name":"Streetwise","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Streetwise entails having the knowledge and shrewd resourcefulness needed to survive in the rough streets of an urban environment. The streetwise skill can be used to identify likely cooperative individuals and whom to avoid, which areas of a city to steer clear of and where opportunity may be found. Streetwise gives insight and ability to handle gangs, thugs and street-rats as well as the jargon and behaviour necessary to avoid a slit throat.</p>\n<p>Street wisdom is useful for thugs, thieves, beggars and others who reside in or frequently visit rough, urban environments.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Back-alley dealing and smuggling.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mPTUHwQDqrmn2UV7"}
{"name":"Acrobatics","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Acrobatics is the art of movement involving difficult feats of balance and nimbleness. This skill can be used when a character attempts to do somersaults, back handsprings, scaling steep surfaces and ropes, balancing acts and various leaps and jumps. The more complex the acrobatic feat, the harder the difficulty. Acrobatics can be used during combat to perform manoeuvres such as leaping over opponents and disengaging a foe by doing a backwards somersault. Acrobatics can also be used for body contortion, which can be highly useful if a character is tied up or being grappled. If acrobatics is used in combat, an acrobatic feat is a full action like any other combat action.</p>\n<p>Acrobatics are particularly useful for performers and temple dancers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Tightrope walking and multitasking - the ability to perform another action while engaged in acrobatics, such as juggling while hanging on a trapeze.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nktS9UCBFSXFDNF0"}
{"name":"Animal Handling","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>The ability to herd, handle and otherwise control animals. The character is able to soothe, excite and direct the actions of animals. Although domesticated animals such as Akopi, Marud oxen, et cetera will more likely respond to commands, here is still a chance to influence the actions of wild animals. With this skill controlling draught animals under normal conditions does not require a roll. If the animals are untamed or otherwise unstable as draught animals &ndash; due to skittishness or the like &ndash; a skill-roll is necessary. Steering through difficult terrain, performing hazardous manoeuvres, driving at excessive speed or if involved in combat also require a skill-roll.</p>\n<p>The Animal Handling skill is particularly useful for charioteers, caravan drovers, farmers, snake charmers and other animal trainers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Animal training, riding, coachman, charioteer and herding. The riding specialisation allows a character to perform other actions while riding without the usual penalties.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nqoqel0fvtX0e5Cf"}
{"name":"Scholastic Lore","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>This skill grants insight into academic tradition, method and knowledge. People versed in academic disciplines have studied extensively and have a deep understanding of the intricacies and historical significance of their chosen subject, such as religion, law, philosophy or warfare. Thus - in case of overlapping topics - scholastic lore is much more detailed and comprehensive than common lore. Where a character versed in common lore would know when certain battles took place during a campaign and who won, an individual versed in academic lore would also understand the cause of the conflict, which tactics were employed and the historical aftermath of the war. This skill gives the character insight into the past, to better understand the current state of things. Beast lore would deal with the knowledge about animals both wild and domesticated, giving insight into type distinction, behavioural-, eating- and breeding-habits as well as the typical habitats of animals and beasts. Religious lore grants profound insight into religious and spiritual scriptures, practices and rituals, the layout of widespread temples and other sanctities as well as knowledge of the properties of the divine beings themselves. Lore of warfare would confer knowledge of the doctrines of war, troop deployment and practical understanding of tactics and strategy as well as detailed knowledge about numerous significant battles.</p>\n<p>Scholastic lore is particularly useful for philosophers, scholars, tacticians and lawmakers.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Antiquarian studies, academic writing, lecturing and specific subjects.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ppE9Wm6XWAqsoNtY"}
{"name":"Observation","permission":{"default":0,"RrWQxiSTW954To8L":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":"<p>Your character has been trained in the art of scrutiny and examination, with few details escaping her penetrating gaze. The observation skill can be used for a variety of purposes such as searching an area to find concealed objects or traps, following tracks, noticing out- of-place behaviour and for general detection. When the observation skill is used you must determine whether you have a specific focus or simply look for something interesting or amiss in your current situation/location. The difficulty of the roll is determined by circumstances such as illumination and visibility of the speaker.</p>\n<p>This ability is of significant use to hunters, guards, diplomats and thieves.</p>\n<p><em>Suggested specialisations: Scrutiny &ndash; this specialisation enables a character to discern and assess behaviour to determine motivation, deception and the personality of people. This skill will not give insight into another&rsquo;s mind, but it will provide an indication about their motives. Lip reading &ndash; this allow characters to &ldquo;eavesdrop&rdquo; from afar, following conversations without hearing the words. The character needs to be able to see the speaker&rsquo;s lips clearly and understand the language spoken for the attempt to have any chance of success. If the speaker is directing her communication at the lip reader, no roll is required.</em></p>","ranks":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qGweTgCcBOP54100"}
